1 the evacuation process utilizing a series of 800 mm diameter steel pipes has presented a significant challenge for the rescue efforts ndrf personnel have simulated a drill to demonstrate their approach for traversing through the pipes to reach the other side of the debris where the trapped labourers are located ndrf secondincommand 2 ic ravi shankar badhani told ptialso read uttarkashi tunnel collapse news live update silkyara rescue operation now in final stages says official2 medical professionals have been stationed within the tunnel and ambulances are positioned outside to ensure the safe transfer of the rescued individuals the ambulances will convey the workers to a hospital established in chinyalisaur approximately 30 kilometres from the tunnel location3

the ambulances will convey the workers to a hospital established in chinyalisaur approximately 30 kilometres from the tunnel location3 the dedicated freight corridor corporation of india limited dfccil and indian railways ir have collaborated to operate a special train transporting equipment from karambeli in gujarat to rishikesh in uttarakhand covering a distance of 1605 km this initiative aims to support the rescue efforts for the trapped workers in the uttarkashi tunnel collapse incidentalso read after the collapse of the uttarkashi tunnel nhai to inspect all underconstruction tunnels across india4 on wednesday a 41bed hospital was established at the chinyalisaur community health centre in the district to provide medical care for the 41 trapped laborers once they are rescued from the silkyara tunnel

additionally a temporary hospital with eight beds has been arranged at the location to offer immediate medical attention to the trapped workers if necessary pti reported5 after conversing with the workers their family members expressed optimism anticipating that the anxious wait would ultimately lead to a heartwarming reunion with their loved ones we called him on diwali but could not reach him his colleagues told us that his mobile phone had been damaged later we saw his name in the newspaper and learnt that he was trapped inside the tunnel he told ptialso read uttarkashi tunnel collapse good news in next 40 hrs if say officials6 jharkhand chief minister hemant soren voiced concern on wednesday regarding the delayed evacuation of workers from the underconstruction silkyara tunnel in uttarakhand7 ten days have passed since the collapse in the tunnel but there is no surety when the workers who are trapped will come out soren said

 styletextalignjustifyu003eit is evident that although the primary role of a salesperson is to sell and secure orders they dedicate a significant portion of their time to support tasks such as ensuring clean orders in the system customer followup and internal coordination

on average a salesperson managing 1015 sales orders and 1015 inquiries also handles approximately 50100 support tasks related to these open orders and inquiries to optimize their time sales teams batch different tasks by types across orders into time buckets which in turn results in monthend spikes in order booking and dispatches however over time trying to close these support tasks leads to multitasking and expediting consuming a considerable amount of the salespersons time and effort although these support tasks may seem minor individually their cumulative effect significantly diminishes the salespersons productivityu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ein this situation salespeople often face this conflict  pursue new business timeconsuming affair or focus on orders in hands and their support tasks for immediate gains

so even if the top management asks them to expand the customer base the need for immediate gains makes them focus on the necessity to take care of support tasks these support activities which involve paperwork and communication with both customers and internal departments necessitate access to it systems and specific formats in the office consequently salespeople end up spending more time in the branch office pursuing these nonsales activities than on field visitsu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ea solution that does not worku003ch2u003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003eupto 23rd of a salesmans monthly capacity is thus wasted on noncore activities consequently the sales team has minimal capacity for real sales thereby hindering the process of new customer acquisition and overall business growth

consequently the sales team has minimal capacity for real sales thereby hindering the process of new customer acquisition and overall business growthu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003erecognizing this issue many large companies have attempted to release sales capacity by setting up branch commercial teams backend teams this did not prove very helpful becauseu003cpu003eu003culu003eu003cliu003ethe support team did not have the authority to interact with customers directly they relied on the information from the sales team this indirectly consumed the salesmans timeu003cliu003eu003cliu003ethe support team also had other unrelated responsibilities limiting their availability to undertake support tasks in a timely manner when tasks were missed or were incomplete the salespeople often had to follow up with themu003cliu003eu003culu003eu003cpu003eso what can be done

u003cpu003eu003ch2u003ethe way outu003ch2u003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ea real solution to releasing sales capacity from support tasks requires us to question some fundamental assumptions on which the current structure of sales as a function is basedu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003e do customers truly desire a single point of contact for all sales and sales support mattersu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003e should accountability for the entire processfrom order intake to final billingtruly rest solely with the individual salesperson

u003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ethe first point is clearly flawed for a customer accessing the right information in a timely manner is more important than speaking to the salesperson the banking industry serves as a great example of this customers often interact with the call centre website branch office and other channels without needing to contact a salespersonu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ethe price organizations pay for the second assumption is a tremendous loss of sales capacity only if companies have the gumption to consider giving up this assumption made in a bid for better control over the salesman and therefore the sales process can a winwin solution ie a solution that allowsu003ca styletextdecorationnone targetblank hrefhttpswwwvectorconsulting

e a solution that allowsu003ca styletextdecorationnone targetblank hrefhttpswwwvectorconsultinginenresearchandpublicationlearningfromimplementationexploitingsalescapacityu003e sales capacityu003cau003e release with even better control over the sales process be evolved to ensure continuous business growthu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ereleasing sales capacityu003ch2u003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ethe first step to release the sales teams capacity is to set up a backend customer support team to manage all support tasks however this dedicated sales team has to complete all the tasks with precision and reliability is needed only then will allow the sales teams to focus on their real task  generating sales
u003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustify

u003ein order to ensure that support tasks are completed with the required clockwork precision and reliability companies need tou003cpu003eu003culu003eu003cliu003ecreate this team at a centralised location
instead of at the branches

to leverage the benefits of aggregation and make this dedicated support team viableu003cliu003eu003cliu003egive direct access to customers to the team in order to provide proactive u0026amp progressive information and eliminate the need for salesperson interventionu003cliu003eu003cliu003estandardize support tasks as much as possibleu003cliu003eu003cliu003euse technology like robotic process automation for repetitive tasks

for repetitive tasks if possibleu003cliu003eu003cliu003edivide the tasks between teams based on skill  division should be such that there is minimal need for the team to multitasku003cliu003eu003cliu003ecreate slas along with clear handover criteria for each tasku003cliu003eu003cliu003eset up a system for realtime evaluation of the teams and for clearing any obstacles to the flow of tasksu003cliu003eu003culu003eu003cpu003eimplementing such a system will go a long way in reducing expediting calls from customers allowing the salesperson to focus on generating sales

u003cpu003eu003ch2u003eimproving sales team productivityu003ch2u003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ean effective backend may release 70 capacity of the salespeople yet inefficiencies remain because the customers are geographically dispersed and the salesperson has to travel to their office and often they have to wait for the client to avoid this wastage of time salespeople tend to prioritize buyers who are most likely to give orders as a result they miss out on opportunities to build longterm relations and influence future ordersu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003eto use a salespersons time better the customers of a company can be divided into  repeat customers and new customers this can be used as the basis to identify ways to service them without any wasteful travel maximising sales and enhancing development opportunities

this can be used as the basis to identify ways to service them without any wasteful travel maximising sales and enhancing development opportunitiesu003cpu003eu003culu003eu003cliu003eu003ciu003eu003cstrongu003emanaging repeat customersu003cstrongu003eu003ciu003eu003cliu003eu003culu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ewith repeat customers they have already bought into your brand the sales team can maintain contact via phone beats essentially regular phone calls to reach out to a wider customer base without wasting time and effortu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ethese phone beats can be done by a dedicated team lets call them inside sales team carved out from the larger sales team based out of a more centralized location who focuses on reaching out to the entire customer base in a predefined rhythm

this way the backend and internal sales team can work in tandem to deliver efficient customer service and order closing  a winwin for both the customer and the companyu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003etravel for meetings then needs to be done only when the customer specifically requests for one these can be set up for the onfield sales team by the inside team so now onfield sales team will travel only for scheduled agendaspecific meetings making the travel more effective and efficientu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003esetting up a system for realtime evaluation of the teams and for clearing any obstacles to the flow of tasks will ensure control over the process and a good flow of sales from this set of customers

u003cpu003eu003culu003eu003cliu003eu003ciu003eu003cstrongu003emanaging new business generationu003cstrongu003eu003ciu003eu003cliu003eu003culu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ecompared to selling to existing customers new customer acquisition takes more effort and time it also requires a sound understanding of the companys offerings clients requirements and sharp selling skills this requires dedicated efforts since any interruptions or delayed response can impact conversion hence a dedicated business development team is carved out from the existing team moreover one big part of new customer acquisition is cold calling an unpleasant chore for an expert salespersonu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ea centralized campaign coordination team can help

u003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ea centralized campaign coordination team can help they can create a database of potential customers identify prospects via phone calls or emails and schedule visits for the expert salesperson so that sales experts do not have to make any cold calls and instead focus their efforts on good leads once the relationship is developed u0026amp mindshare for the brand is acquired enquiries from new customers will start to flow in any ball drop in these enquiries will lead to a poor conversion ratio hence a funnel manager is deployed to ensure timely response and progress of these enquiriesu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003efunnel managers support multiple sales efforts simultaneously acting as navigators while the sales team drives in this drivernavigator model the funnel manager provides strategic guidance and coordination allowing the sales team to concentrate on execution

in this drivernavigator model the funnel manager provides strategic guidance and coordination allowing the sales team to concentrate on execution the funnel manager interacts directly with clients to understand their needs at any given moment and ensures they receive the best resources from the team the customer support team manages all presales and postsales support activities needed once the new customer starts providing regular orders the team managing repeat orders can take over this approach drives the progress of sales tasks and maintains alignment with client expectationsu003cpu003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003esuch a streamlined internal sales process and having prescheduled sales visits make the sales funnel transparent this can easily be monitored using any standard crm package the transparency also allows people to take proactive action if orders are stuck all this will boost sales in the long run

this can easily be monitored using any standard crm package the transparency also allows people to take proactive action if orders are stuck all this will boost sales in the long runu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ea game changeru003ch2u003eu003cp styletextalignjustifyu003ethis way of working leads to a reorganization of the sales function and requires collaboration between centralized back end internal sales teams field salespeople and business development managers to deliver enhanced sales productivity and customer service however this approach converts the sales process from what is viewed currently as a black box to a transparent process allowing for timely decisionmaking and continuous improvement it also will enable the company to adapt quickly to changing market dynamics and customer needs ensuring business growth and competitive advantage

 are omnipresent in our lives from our kitchen shelves and closets to the gadgets held in our hands and whats sitting in our garages

consciously and even at a subconscious level we tend to imbue the brands we use with certain qualities such as trustworthiness product quality or simply an aura of exclusivity that puts us in an elite club branding plays a key role in shaping our perceptions and how we navigate our modern lifestylesu003cpu003eu003cpu003ehowever what we perceive may not be the actual truth or the whole truth we often tend to equate high prices with high quality even if that is not really the case the price in such cases is often for prestigerelated brand associations rather than just product qualityu003cpu003eu003cpu003efor instance recently television journalist palki sharma highlighted how dior bags sell at 2800 while costing only 57 to make as a prestigious fashion label dior commands a premium in the market that is based on the perceived value of ownership perceptions play a significant role in many markets

as a prestigious fashion label dior commands a premium in the market that is based on the perceived value of ownership perceptions play a significant role in many marketsu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ealso read u003ca classmanualbacklink targetblank hrefhttpswwwlivemintcomeconomypalmoilpricesgodrejconsumerpackagedfoodshulbritanniafmcgcookingoilconsumersq3earningsprofiturbandemand11734000919240htmlu003emint explainer how rising palm oil prices impact india and its consumersu003cau003eu003ch2u003eu003cpu003ethat is true even for some commodities that have a certain image among consumers and therefore have brandlike characteristics an interesting example is that of palm oil which has a massy rather than classy appeal ironically because of its affordable pricing

an interesting example is that of palm oil which has a massy rather than classy appeal ironically because of its affordable pricingu003cpu003eu003cpu003edespite this miracle oil being in heavy use as a production input across food and nonedible products in india including biofuel it has been getting a lot of negative press lately as some brands and influencers clamber onto an antipalm oil bandwagonu003cpu003eu003cpu003ethis narrative persists even as prominent soap manufacturers such as godrej say they cannot compromise on product quality by getting rid of palm oil even pepsico which decided to do away with it has resorted to its palmolein blend insteadu003cpu003eu003cpu003eso if palm oil is irreplaceable in several production processes why has it been painted as a villainous ingredient

u003cpu003eu003cpu003elets start with what makes it affordable and the answer may surprise you it is highly landefficient supplying between 35 and 40 of the worlds vegetable oil demand by making use of just under 86 of all the land used for the production of all vegetable oils across the world yes you read that right this means that on average other oils use many multiples of extra farmland to turn out the same volumeu003cpu003eu003cpu003epalm oil has been portrayed as being bad for the environment but its harm is often overstated as hannah ritchie from the university of oxfords our world in data points out her research suggests that if all substitutable oil demand were met with palm oil globally it would require only 77 million hectaresa fraction compared to other oilsu003cpu003eu003cpu003ethat palm oil leads to deforestation as natural forests are cleared for palm plantations is also an outdated narrative

u003cpu003eu003cpu003ethat palm oil leads to deforestation as natural forests are cleared for palm plantations is also an outdated narrative in malaysia a major exporter palmoil corporations have taken action towards sustainable farming with 83 of palm oil refining capacities operating under a no deforestation peat and exploitation ndpe commitment as reported by global forest watch in june 2023 this has led a sharp reduction in forest lossu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ealso read u003ca classmanualbacklink targetblank hrefhttpswwwlivemintcomindustryfmcghindustanunileverteacoffeeoilsoappackagedgoodscrudeoiladaniwilmarpalmoiltataconsumerruraldemand11729846164947htmlu003eedible oil tea coffee soap to see higher prices this quarteru003cau003eu003ch2u003eu003cpu003ethe indian government recognizes the importance of expanding the domestic cultivation of this crop

its recently launched national mission on edible oilsoilseeds aims to reduce our dependence on imports in 202324 india imported approximately u003cspan classwebrupeeu003eu003cspanu003e80000 crore worth of edible oils with palm oil alone accounting for over half that figureu003cpu003eu003cpu003ea government scheme under the mission focuses on raising indias oil palm output by offering our farmers protection from market fluctuations and incentivizing sustainable productionu003cpu003eu003cpu003enow that we have established that palm oil has successfully overturned the deforestation narrative what about perceptions of it around dinner tables

for starters all oils when consumed in moderation can be part of a balanced diet that said all oils from sunflower to groundnut and palm oil come with their unique characteristicsu003cpu003eu003cpu003epalm oil gives ice cream its silkysmooth texture it also makes chips crisp and biscuits crunchy it is also popular among processed food manufacturers because it remains semisolid at room temperatureu003cpu003eu003cpu003eas for health effects olive oil gets most attention at dinner tables as being good for us however low yields and supply volumes keep olive oil expensive research shows that palm oil which is considered high in saturated fat contains a high percentage of hearthealthy monounsaturated fatty acids like olive oilu003cpu003eu003cpu003eit also has a high smoking point and can be stored for longer unlike some other oils without going rancid

u003cpu003eu003cpu003eit also has a high smoking point and can be stored for longer unlike some other oils without going rancid these are perhaps the reasons why palm oil is available through ration shops under indias public distribution systemu003cpu003eu003cpu003epalm oil contrary to popular perception can also reduce cholesterol thanks to its unique vitamin e composition and abundance of tocotrienols as mentioned in the icmrnational institute of nutritions 2024 dietary guidelines for indiansu003cpu003eu003cpu003eheres another interesting nugget unrefined red palm oil is said to contain 15 times more retinol provitamin a equivalents than carrots 300 times more than tomatoes and 44 times more than leafy vegetablesu003cpu003eu003ch2u003ealso read u003ca classmanualbacklink targetblank hrefhttpswwwlivemint

u003cpu003eu003ch2u003ealso read u003ca classmanualbacklink targetblank hrefhttpswwwlivemintcomeconomyedibleoilpricesinflationfoodinflationimportdutyheadlineinflationpricehikessoyabeanoilpalmoil11729065581941htmlu003ein charts will rising edible oil prices fry your kitchen budget

u003cau003eu003ch2u003eu003cpu003ethe case of palm oil is a remarkable example of the disservice that illinformed perceptions can do to our wellbeing it isnt causing deforestation and is better for our health than many think significantly a lot can be produced with very little land which makes it weigh lighter on our pockets too

text sizesmallmediumlargefollow us image used for representational purpose only new delhikochi the union health ministry asked all states to be on alert while health minister mansukh mandaviya called a meeting of state health ministers on wednesday to review preparedness in view of a surge in respiratory illnesses in the country including covid19

kerala is witnessing a rise in covid cases as well as deaths daily cases detected in the state have nearly tripled in a week while 10 deaths have been reported from december 1 to 17 as per data sent to the centre sources in the state health department saidof particular concern is jn1 a new covid subvariant recently detected in a 79yearold woman in keralaon december 16 kerala reported 302 new covid cases and four deaths the highest in the latest outbreak on december 10 kerala had reported 109 cases daily cases crossed 200 on december 12 and within four days kerala reported over 300 fresh casescovid states told to increase rtpcr teststhe health secretary in his letter to states highlighted the need for maintaining constant vigil over the covid19 situation

covid states told to increase rtpcr teststhe health secretary in his letter to states highlighted the need for maintaining constant vigil over the covid19 situation he asked them to monitor and report districtwise influenzalike illness ili severe acute respiratory illness sari cases in all health facilities on a regular basis including in the integrated health information platform ihip portal for detecting the early rising trend of cases states have also been advised to increase the number of rtpcr tests and send positive samples for genome sequencing to indian sars cov2 genomics consortium insacog laboratories to enable timely detection of new variants if any in the country jn1 was first identified in august and reports suggest it carried significant mutations that may contribute to increased transmissibility and immuneescape ability jn1 variant has also been reported in the usa china and singapore

jn1 variant has also been reported in the usa china and singapore union health secretary sudhansh pant shared details about jn1 with the additional chief secretary principal secretary and secretary health of all states uts with a message to keep up the vigil against emergence of any new clusters of covid19 or other respiratory illness for timely action the information shared by the union health secretary states that the current laboratory test rtpcr is effective for jn1 detection on symptoms and severity in cases involving covid19 caused by the new subvariant the health secretary in the annexure shared by the government with the states says that it is not known whether jn1 infection produces different symptoms from other variants according to the government there is no indication of increased severity from jn1 or risk posed by the subvariant to public health in comparison to other currently circulating variants

according to the government there is no indication of increased severity from jn1 or risk posed by the subvariant to public health in comparison to other currently circulating variants updated covid19 vaccines are expected to increase protection against jn1 as they do for other variants the government says

contexthttpsschemaorgtypewebpagenamecentre calls health meet as covid rises in kerala 10 deaths this monthurlhttpstimesofindiaindiatimescomcitykochicentrecallshealthmeetascovidrisesinkerala10deathsthismontharticleshow106106851cmscontexthttpsschemaorgarticlebodynew delhikochi the union health ministry asked all states to be on alert while health minister mansukh mandaviya called a meeting of state health ministers on wednesday to review preparedness in view of a surge in respiratory illnesses in the country including covid19kerala is witnessing a rise in covid cases as well as deaths daily cases detected in the state have nearly tripled in a week while 10 deaths have been reported from december 1 to 17 as per data sent to the centre sources in the state health department saidof particular concern is jn1 a new covid subvariant recently detected in a 79yearold woman in kerala

of particular concern is jn1 a new covid subvariant recently detected in a 79yearold woman in keralaon december 16 kerala reported 302 new covid cases and four deaths the highest in the latest outbreak on december 10 kerala had reported 109 cases daily cases crossed 200 on december 12 and within four days kerala reported over 300 fresh casescovid states told to increase rtpcr teststhe health secretary in his letter to states highlighted the need for maintaining constant vigil over the covid19 situation he asked them to monitor and report districtwise influenzalike illness ili severe acute respiratory illness sari cases in all health facilities on a regular basis including in the integrated health information platform ihip portal for detecting the early rising trend of cases

states have also been advised to increase the number of rtpcr tests and send positive samples for genome sequencing to indian sars cov2 genomics consortium insacog laboratories to enable timely detection of new variants if any in the country jn1 was first identified in august and reports suggest it carried significant mutations that may contribute to increased transmissibility and immuneescape ability jn1 variant has also been reported in the usa china and singapore union health secretary sudhansh pant shared details about jn1 with the additional chief secretary principal secretary and secretary health of all states uts with a message to keep up the vigil against emergence of any new clusters of covid19 or other respiratory illness for timely action the information shared by the union health secretary states that the current laboratory test rtpcr is effective for jn1 detection

the information shared by the union health secretary states that the current laboratory test rtpcr is effective for jn1 detection on symptoms and severity in cases involving covid19 caused by the new subvariant the health secretary in the annexure shared by the government with the states says that it is not known whether jn1 infection produces different symptoms from other variants according to the government there is no indication of increased severity from jn1 or risk posed by the subvariant to public health in comparison to other currently circulating variants updated covid19 vaccines are expected to increase protection against jn1 as they do for other variants the government says typenewsarticlemainentityofpagehttpstimesofindiaindiatimescomcitykochicentrecallshealthmeetascovidrisesinkerala10deathsthismontharticleshow106106851
